<h3>The Goal of this Project</h3>
<p>My goal for this project is to show how two different API calls can be combined to create a meaningful web experience. In League of Legends there are over 110 characters, called champions, that the player can play. Remember how I said that Riot pulls in over $1 billion per year on this game? That is because not everything is free. When you first start playing you are given to own, for free, about 10 champions. Every week Riot will allow 12 champions to be played for free. These are called free to play or the weekly rotation. I will be using on API call to get a list of the free champions for this week, and then another call to get information specific to a champion according to it's ID. Basically we will be getting a list, then going through that list to get more details on each list item.</p>

